    "<p>There are four layers:<ul><li>фҖ…Ҝ вҖ” Default alphanumeric keys</li><li>фҖ—ў вҖ” Function (Fn) layer (top left <i class=\"fn\">orange</i> legends)</li><li>фҖғ« вҖ” Number Pad (NP) (bottom left <i class=\"pad\">blue</i> legends)</li><li>фҖҚұ вҖ” Meta layer (bottom <i class=\"meta\">purple</i> legends)</li></ul><p>Notes:<ul><li>Encoder replaces first key on one of the top three rows.<li>Bottom right legends indicate modifier when held.</li><li>Fn layer can be accessed from NP.</li><li>Meta layer is accessed by pressing фҖғ« while фҖ—ў is held.</li><li>NP and Meta layers can be toggled on with three taps</li><li>Unmarked keys on NP and Meta layers have no action. However, Shift on NP is Shift+<em>Default layer</em> key (e.g., Shift+фҖғ  is вҖҳ*вҖҷ) for all keys.</li><li>Right Alt (Option) on Fn layer is Right Alt+<em>Default layer</em> key (e.g., RAlt+F3 is вҖҳВЈвҖҷ).</li><li>Application shortcuts on Meta layer are actually function keys that trigger <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/hotkey-app/id975890633\">HotKey App</a> actions."
